Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of maximum rate achievable with analog network coding in a layered relay network with directed links. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) and network communication (cs.NI). The paper proposes a scheme to compute a lower bound to the optimal rate achievable with analog network coding, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of cut-set upper bound, which is a concept from network coding (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the specific case of Gaussian N-relay diamond network, which is related to multimedia communication (cs.MM).
